      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;So you are chain pulling for your group.&amp;nbsp; The current mob is getting low on health, so you run off to pull another mob.&amp;nbsp; While you are off getting the mob, the rest of the group finishes off the previous mob...and no one gets xp because you are too far from the group.&amp;nbsp; This is incredibly frustrating.&amp;nbsp; The group is then pissed at you, because they got no xp.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This has always been an incredible frustration to me.&amp;nbsp; I took a break from EQ for a few months, and I come back, and it seems the range has been reduced even more.&amp;nbsp; I thought this was my imagination, until it was confirmed that the range was decreased.&amp;nbsp; I just cannot understand this.&amp;nbsp; To me, this is THE most frustrating thing about EQ.&amp;nbsp; Is the purpose to prevent chain pulling for some strange reason?&amp;nbsp; I'm thinking it has something to do with trying to prevent people from grouping up with other soloers so they can solo and still get the group bonus.&amp;nbsp; If so, there HAS to be a better way to prevent that.&amp;nbsp; Maybe if the person is OOR and they didn't do any damage to the mob then no one gets xp.&amp;nbsp; As it is, its main function is to prevent people from chain pulling.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
