    <item>
      <title>Re: Puller OOR?  No xp for group!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=12190#M12190</link>
      <description>It doesn't matter whether you are on the hate list or not. You don't have to have touched the mob a single time or even looked at it to get exp if you are in the group that killed it. It is simply if you are the one that pulled the mob, getting what I call &amp;quot;initial aggro&amp;quot;, and then go out of exp range and don't return to that range before the mob is dead, your entire group loses out on exp. However, if somebody else in the group goes out of exp range while the mob is killed, only that person misses out on the exp. Also, death or any other form of zoning as well as successfully FDing are all ways to remove the &amp;quot;initial aggro&amp;quot; flag from somebody.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It was never coded where if a single person was oor that nobody got the exp. I really just think that it was coded to avoid somebody sitting an alt at zone meanwhile the main is off somewhere slaying mobs and gaining no risk exp to the alt. Of course this is ridiculous because somebody will simply have their alt sitting nearby to avoid that. I have done so already *shrug*. What should be done is either expand the exp range a good amount or make it zone wide experience....which I don't think the latter is a great idea, but if it's the only way to fix this problem, it should be done. We have some very large zones in the game and if a group is able to kill the mobs in their group's area before the spawns can repopulate, the group shouldn't, then, be inadvertantly punished when the puller is forced to go out of exp range to get more mobs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
