      <description>&lt;div&gt;Really what should be done, is if you are on the hatelist of the mob, and you are in the group that did the most damage to the mob, then you should get xp, regardless of where in the zone you are.  At this point, I don't think it is a game design issue (it is past that point...it is an admitted bug and is not &amp;quot;working as intended&amp;quot;).  It is a code issue.  Who knows whether it will ever get fixed or not though.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Are there workarounds that you can do?  Yes, but they all suck.  I see my job as puller, to time pulls to come in right as the previous mob dies.  This is just not possible in many zones in many groups, with this bug.  There are always going to be times where the mob dies quicker then you anticipated...due to a wizard/mage crit or what have you.  I like truely challenging pulls.  What I don't like is stupid bugs like this that cause my group to lose xp for no good reason.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I'm sure there is most likely a defect report or, whatever they call it, on this issue.  And I am betting it has a very low priority/urgency, and it is unlikely it will ever get addressed.  The reason it has a low priority, is because of limited customer complaints because most people think it is intentional to prevent some solo group xp exploit.  it isn't, but that is the common misconception.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
